cs.IR, cs.DL, cs.CL, cs.CY, cs.CR 

This paper deals with the issue of collecting and archiving web content, specifically news stories, which falls under the domain of information retrieval (cs.IR). The paper also involves web scraping and data mining techniques, which are commonly used in digital libraries (cs.DL). The analysis of the search engine result pages (SERPs) and the tracking of URIs over time involve natural language processing (NLP) and text classification (cs.CL), as well as cybersecurity (cs.CY) and cryptography (cs.CR) to ensure the integrity and security of the collected data.
